# Spanish UI Text Guidelines

## User-Facing Text Must Be in Spanish
All labels, messages, notifications, and user interface text must be displayed in Spanish.

## Examples
- ✅ "Agendamiento creado exitosamente"
- ✅ "Error interno del servidor"
- ✅ "Campos requeridos faltantes"
- ❌ "Appointment created successfully"
- ❌ "Internal server error"

## Notification Messages
Use the existing notification system from [App.jsx](mdc:apps/web/src/App.jsx) instead of browser alerts:

```javascript
// ✅ Correct - Use notification context
notificationContext.showNotification({
    type: 'success',
    title: 'Éxito',
    message: 'Agendamiento creado exitosamente'
});

// ❌ Avoid browser alerts
alert('Success message');
```

## Error Messages
Always provide descriptive error messages in Spanish:

```javascript
res.status(400).json({
    success: false,
    message: 'Sede, modalidad y fecha son requeridos'
});
```

## Form Labels and Placeholders
All form elements should have Spanish labels and placeholders:

```javascript
<Label htmlFor="sede">Sede</Label>
<Input placeholder="Seleccione una sede" />
```

## Success Messages
Use positive, action-oriented language:

- ✅ "Agendamiento creado exitosamente"
- ✅ "Orden de inspección guardada"
- ✅ "Datos actualizados correctamente"
